shared_text:
Alice C Sabatini Art Gallery
April 10 at 2:00 PM ·

The building is still closed, but art is still accessible. The Youth Art Month exhibit is still installed. Thank you, and congratulations, to all of the artists and art teachers who participated in the 2020 Youth Art Month festival. Each teacher got to pick one artwork to represent the school where they teach. We hope you enjoy the talent of our young Kansas artists!

When the building reopens, we will work with the Kansas Art Education Association to return the artworks to the schools and students. It was disappointing not to be able to host the awards reception. More information about the scholarship winners and artworks are here: http://www.kaea.com/2020/ .

Atchison Art Association
March 2, 2019 at 2:43 PM ·

Wooowhoooo! We are open for the 2019 season! Our first event/show is the Sister Helen Beuning Youth Show....please note, our grand opening for this show will be on March 17th pending Nature's fury.
Our open days and times are starting today, Sat/Sund/Wed 1:00 - 5:00. Again, pending Nature's fury.
Newly cleaned, waxed and always loved, the gallery has so much to see and hear about. Come look at our new and upcoming artists in this gorgeous historical setting unlike any other place you've been to.

post_text: Art 1 portrait with a quote project, can you guess who the students are? Also, Mixed Media students have worked on freezer paper stenciling on fabric, & their own stamp design. They used their stamp on a fabric bandana & will dye it using the ice dye method, & their stamp will be resisted. SO FUN!

post_text: Here is a sneak peek at sculptures being made in Ceramics & Sculpture, thanks to HMS 5th graders & their Language Arts teachers!!! The 5th graders wrote a descriptive paragraph & the HHS students had to visualize, sketch, & make it into a sculpture. Two minds, one project. Can't wait to see them completed!!!

post_text:
HHS & HMS students have art on display at the Muchnic Art Gallery in Atchison, KS during the month of March! Today was the opening! Thanks for all of the students & family that attended! The gallery is open Wednesdays, Saturdays, & Sundays from 1-5pm.

Check out the website for more info:
https://www.atchisonart.org
